00:36:19.340 --> 00:36:21.190
But what I really
want is you to be

00:36:21.190 --> 00:36:24.931
so engaged that you're doing
stuff that I can't pay you for.

00:36:24.931 --> 00:36:26.430
You're doing it
because you love it.

00:36:26.430 --> 00:36:28.919
You're doing it because
it's super engaging for you.

00:36:28.919 --> 00:36:30.960
So that's the kind of
environment I want to have.

00:36:30.960 --> 00:36:35.040
I want to create that
3:00 AM employee.

00:36:35.040 --> 00:36:39.610
So interesting outcome
from the neuroscience

00:36:39.610 --> 00:36:43.770
is that the pathway for trust
in the brain, this larger brain

00:36:43.770 --> 00:36:47.590
circuit that we've
characterized as using oxytocin,

00:36:47.590 --> 00:36:51.460
is overlapped strongly
with a brain circuit that

00:36:51.460 --> 00:36:55.770
activates when we are helping
or caring for other people.

00:36:55.770 --> 00:36:59.650
So besides Strucker, my
other management hero

00:36:59.650 --> 00:37:01.620
