number, of those eight factors,

00:43:09.040 --> 00:43:10.272
invest was really low.

00:43:10.272 --> 00:43:12.230
And you talked to the
employees and they'd say,

00:43:12.230 --> 00:43:14.240
you know what, I got
hired here out of college.

00:43:14.240 --> 00:43:15.780
I'm working in this division.

00:43:15.780 --> 00:43:16.960
There's no career ladder.

00:43:16.960 --> 00:43:20.040
No one's really mentoring me.

00:43:20.040 --> 00:43:22.560
It's a burnout job, entry level.

00:43:22.560 --> 00:43:24.330
I just leave.

00:43:24.330 --> 00:43:24.890
I said, OK.

00:43:24.890 --> 00:43:28.160
Let's put in programs so
that you have mentors.

00:43:28.160 --> 00:43:29.950
You have a clear career ladder.

00:43:29.950 --> 00:43:31.840
You have a career coach.

00:43:31.840 --> 00:43:33.550
Let's hire some
people who are senior,

00:43:33.550 --> 00:43:34.880
