How do we do that?

00:49:09.580 --> 00:49:12.365
First of all, you
keep teams small.

00:49:12.365 --> 00:49:16.150
I was talking with folks
in people dev this morning,

00:49:16.150 --> 00:49:20.140
and average team size they
said is nine people here.

00:49:20.140 --> 00:49:20.950
So that's good.

00:49:20.950 --> 00:49:23.832
So single digit teams, much
better than super large teams.

00:49:23.832 --> 00:49:25.790
We can actually have that
personal interaction.

00:49:25.790 --> 00:49:26.820
I know your name.

00:49:26.820 --> 00:49:28.230
I know something about you.

00:49:28.230 --> 00:49:29.771
And then you've got
to actually share

00:49:29.771 --> 00:49:36.410
a little bit outside just I'm
a Ruby on Rails programmer

00:49:36.410 --> 00:49:38.540
and that's my goal in life.

00:49:38.540 --> 00:49:41.119
Or I work in Go or whatever.

